Explanation:

- The getPID method is annotated only with @GET (see public Response getPID()). There are no annotations for @POST, @HEAD, @OPTIONS, @TRACE, @PUT, @DELETE, or @PATCH on that method (and no class-level annotation indicating "allow all methods"), so only GET is explicitly supported by the code.
- "All methods acceptable" is false because nothing in the code indicates a catch-all or wildcard that accepts every HTTP method.
- Per your instruction, I judged HEAD support based strictly on the source code annotations (it is not annotated with @HEAD), so HEAD is reported as false even though some JAX-RS runtimes may implicitly handle HEAD for GET handlers.
